title: Killion scores goal in Australian soccer debut
text:
Killion scores goal in Australian soccer debut 
By Eric Dutkiewicz - 21Alive 3 photos October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 20, 2015 at 12:02 AM EDT 
ADELAIDE, South Australia, Australia (21Alive) - Bishop Dwenger High School graduate Sarah Killion has started off hot in the next stage of her professional soccer career. 
Killion scored a goal in her debut for Adelaide United of the Australian W-League on Saturday. The Lady Reds , as they are called, tied Western Sydney Wanderers 2-2.

Killion's goal came off a corner kick that went directly into the Wanderer's goal. 
Killion, who was drafted No. 2 overall by Sky Blue FC in January's National Women's Soccer League Draft, was loaned to the Lady Reds in September. 
Killion played college soccer at UCLA.
